      expectedOutput: 'GET /api/articles/?category=python -> CACHE MISS -> запрос к БД -> кеш\nGET /api/articles/?category=python -> CACHE HIT -> ответ из кеша\nPOST /api/articles/ -> сигнал -> инвалидация articles:list:* и article:<id>',
      hint: 'Используй hashlib.md5 для хеширования query params в ключ кеша. cache.delete_pattern доступен через django-redis.',
      solution: '# decorators.py\nimport hashlib\nimport logging\nfrom functools import wraps\nfrom django.core.cache import cache\nfrom rest_framework.response import Response\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\ndef cached_view(prefix, timeout=300, vary_on_params=True):\n    def decorator(func):\n        @wraps(func)\n        def wrapper(self, request, *args, **kwargs):\n            # Строим ключ кеша\n            if vary_on_params:\n                params_hash = hashlib.md5(\n                    request.query_params.urlencode().encode()\n                ).hexdigest()[:8]\n                cache_key = f\"{prefix}:{params_hash}\"\n            else:\n                pk = kwargs.get(\"pk\", \"\")\n                cache_key = f\"{prefix}:{pk}\"\n\n            data = cache.get(cache_key)\n            if data is not None:\n                logger.info(f\"CACHE HIT: {cache_key}\")\n                return Response(data)\n\n            logger.info(f\"CACHE MISS: {cache_key}\")\n            response = func(self, request, *args, **kwargs)\n            cache.set(cache_key, response.data, timeout=timeout)\n            return response\n        return wrapper\n    return decorator\n\n# views.py\nfrom rest_framework import viewsets\nfrom rest_framework.response import Response\nfrom .decorators import cached_view\nfrom .models import Article\nfrom .serializers import ArticleSerializer\n\nclass ArticleViewSet(viewsets.ModelViewSet):\n    queryset = Article.objects.all()\n    serializer_class = ArticleSerializer\n\n    @cached_view(prefix=\"articles:list\", timeout=300)\n    def list(self, request, *args, **kwargs):\n        return super().list(request, *args, **kwargs)\n\n    @cached_view(prefix=\"article\", timeout=3600, vary_on_params=False)\n    def retrieve(self, request, *args, **kwargs):\n        return super().retrieve(request, *args, **kwargs)\n\n# signals.py\nfrom django.core.cache import cache\nfrom django.db.models.signals import post_save, post_delete\nfrom django.dispatch import receiver\nfrom .models import Article\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n@receiver([post_save, post_delete], sender=Article)\ndef invalidate_article_cache(sender, instance, **kwargs):\n    cache.delete(f\"article:{instance.id}\")\n    cache.delete_pattern(\"articles:list:*\")\n    logger.info(f\"Cache invalidated for article {instance.id}\")',
      explanation: 'cached_view — универсальный декоратор: prefix задаёт пространство имён ключей, vary_on_params создаёт разные ключи для разных query params. md5 хеш сжимает длинные query strings. Сигналы post_save/post_delete автоматически инвалидируют кеш при любом изменении.'
